# Design & UI Conventions

## Design Tokens Over Hard-Coded Values

Never hard-code colors, spacing, font sizes, or shadows. Always reference design tokens or CSS custom properties.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
<div style={{ padding: "16px", color: "#1a1a1a", fontSize: "14px" }}>

// ✅ GOOD
<div className="p-4 text-primary text-sm">

// ✅ GOOD (CSS modules / custom properties)
// .card { padding: var(--spacing-4); color: var(--color-text-primary); }
```

## Component Composition Over Prop Sprawl

Split large components. If a component accepts more than 5-6 props for visual variants, decompose it into composed sub-components.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — prop explosion
<Card title="..." subtitle="..." icon="..." badge="..." badgeColor="..." size="lg" variant="outlined" />

// ✅ GOOD — composition
<Card variant="outlined">
  <Card.Header>
    <Card.Icon name="settings" />
    <Card.Title>Settings</Card.Title>
  </Card.Header>
  <Card.Badge color="green">Active</Card.Badge>
</Card>
```

## Responsive Design: Mobile-First

Always write styles mobile-first and layer on larger breakpoints. Never write desktop-first and override downward.

```css
/* ❌ BAD — desktop-first */
.grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); }
@media (max-width: 768px) { .grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }

/* ✅ GOOD — mobile-first */
.grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
@media (min-width: 768px) { .grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); } }
```

## Accessibility Requirements

Every interactive element must be keyboard navigable and have appropriate ARIA attributes.

- All `<img>` tags require `alt` text (use `alt=""` only for purely decorative images)
- Form inputs require associated `<label>` elements
- Color contrast must meet WCAG AA (4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text)
- Focus states must be visible — never `outline: none` without a replacement

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
<div onClick={handleClick}>Click me</div>

// ✅ GOOD
<button type="button" onClick={handleClick}>Click me</button>

// ✅ GOOD — when a div must be interactive
<div role="button" tabIndex={0} onClick={handleClick} onKeyDown={handleKeyDown}>
  Click me
</div>
```

## Consistent Spacing Scale

Use a spacing scale (4px base). Don't invent arbitrary spacing values.

| Token | Value | Usage |
|-------|-------|-------|
| `spacing-1` | 4px | Tight inline gaps |
| `spacing-2` | 8px | Icon-to-label, small padding |
| `spacing-3` | 12px | Compact card padding |
| `spacing-4` | 16px | Standard padding, section gaps |
| `spacing-6` | 24px | Card padding, group spacing |
| `spacing-8` | 32px | Section spacing |
| `spacing-12` | 48px | Page section margins |

## Animation Guidelines

- Keep transitions under 300ms for UI feedback
- Use `ease-out` for entrances, `ease-in` for exits
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` — disable non-essential animation

```css
.element {
  transition: transform 200ms ease-out, opacity 200ms ease-out;
}
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .element { transition: none; }
}
```

## Layout Patterns

- Use CSS Grid for 2D layouts (page structure, card grids)
- Use Flexbox for 1D alignment (navbars, inline groups)
- Avoid absolute positioning for layout — use it only for overlays, tooltips, and floating elements
